<h4>Welcome to the UIC Human Resources Website</h4>
<br>
<p> UIC Human Resources is committed to providing timely and effective support through human resource management expertise for faculty, staff and administrators. As one of the top-20 employers in Chicago, a primary goal is to advance the mission of the University through a well-trained and highly qualified workforce.</p>
<br>
<p>UIC Human Resources staff members provide services including employee recruitment, new employee onboarding, compensation, and labor/employee relations. </p>
<br>
<p>Continuous improvement is a key strategic goal of the UIC Human Resources team. We are always seeking ways to make things better for those we serve. Your feedback is needed to help us better meet your needs. On each page throughout our website you will find a <a href="https://www.hr.uic.edu/feedback/">feedback link</a>. Please take the opportunity to share your thoughts on ways we can improve service to the campus community.
</p>
<br>
<p>Your partnership is important to us. Please let us know how we can best meet your needs.</p>
</div></div>

<p><span style="font-size: 12px;">NOTICE OF AVAILABILITY OF THE UIC ANNUAL SECURITY AND FIRE SAFETY REPORT</span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">The University of Illinois at Chicago is pleased to share the <a href="http://go.uic.edu/CleryReport" target="_blank">Annual Security &amp; Fire Safety Report</a> with all current and prospective employees. The report contains information regarding campus security and personal safety including topics such as: crime prevention, public safety authority, crime reporting policies, fire safety, disciplinary procedures, and fire statistics in UIC residential facilities and crime statistics for the three previous calendar years. The full text of this report is available online on the UIC Clery Website at <a href="http://clery.uic.edu" target="_blank">clery.uic.edu</a>. Current and prospective employees may obtain a paper copy of the report from the UIC HR Welcome Center, located at the Human Resources Building, 715 South Wood Street, Room 109, Chicago, IL 60612 or by calling (312) 996-0840.</p></div>
